"Entity" is a general term used to refer to anything that has existence or being. It is a fundamental concept that can be applied to various kinds of things, from physical objects to abstract concepts. Entities can be rigid or non-rigid depending on their nature. In this case, since "Entity" is a very general term, it is considered non-rigid (-R) as it doesn't carry any essential properties that apply to all instances in all possible worlds.

Entities can have identity, but they don't necessarily supply their own identity conditions (-O). Instead, they might inherit their identity from other properties or contexts. They maintain unity (+U) as they are intrinsic wholes, but they can be dependent (-D) or independent based on their specific nature.
